cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper presents a deep learning model that uses reinforcement learning to learn control policies directly from high-dimensional sensory input. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.RO (Robotics). However, given that the paper focuses on the use of deep learning and reinforcement learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that cs.CV is a likely sub-category. Finally, the application of the method to Atari games suggests that cs.NE and cs.RO are also possible sub-categories, but less likely than the others.
